      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <h3>Whats a Twitter Chat?</h3>
      <p>A twitter chat is pretty easy. Just go to twitter at the designated time. Ask your question by adding the #webonfire hashtag to the end of your message. If you need to write a longer message than 140 characters or 3 sequential tweets then I suggest using <a href="https://longreply.com">longreply</a>. Then, wait for your response.</p>
      <p>If you want to see what other people are asking you can do a <a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23webonfire">search on the hashtag</a>. Or follow #webonfire in your favorite twitter program. I suggest <a href="https://about.twitter.com/products/tweetdeck">TweetDeck</a> or TweetBot for <a href="http://tapbots.com/software/tweetbot/">iPhone</a> or <a href="http://tapbots.com/software/tweetbot/ipad/">iPad</a>. In TweetBot or TweetDeck you can search on #webonfire and then save your search.</p>
      <h3>How do I participate?</h3>
      <p>Use this page, sign into twitter or fire up your favorite Twitter client. Follow the #webonfire hashtag or send a tweet with #webonfire to ask a question. Make sure if you reply to another comment or question to include the #hashtag at the end or it will not be included.</p>
      <h3>What Questions can I ask?</h3>
      <p>You can ask me pretty much anything. Ideally questions related to ZURB Foundation, JavaScript / jQuery, Meteor or Ruby.</p>
      <h3>Can I get feedback on my site?</h3>
      <p>Yes. To get the most out of it you should ask something specific. For example: </p>
      <ul>
        <li><del>What do you think of my site?</del></li>
        <li>How can I optimize my site?</li>
        <li>Does my grid structure make sense?</li>
        <li>How can I optimize my mobile experience?</li>
        <li>What is the biggest problem with my site?</li>
      </ul>
